Sustained gunfire erupted Tuesday in Lubumbashi, DR Congo&#8217;s second-largest city, where large numbers of police have been deployed on the last day of President Joseph Kabila&#8217;s mandate, an AFP correspondent said.The firing started at 9:15am (0715 GMT) in a neighbourhood in the south of the city where demonstrators and police have clashed, with streets strewn with rocks and burned tyres, the correspondent said.-AFP